comments: During the screen, Bullock (DAL) and Bogdanovic (UTA) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Gobert (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in Bullock's (DAL) path and absorbs the contact during the screen.
Dinwiddie (DAL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Kleber (DAL) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Mitchell (UTA).
Gobert (UTA) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs with Brunson's (DAL) arm, which does not affect his ability to secure the rebound.
Conley (UTA) slightly extends his arm out and marginal contact occurs with Brunson's (DAL) arm, which does not affect his SQBR or ability to make his intended pass at the end of the drive.
Gobert (UTA) is deemed to be in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Dinwiddie (DAL) jumps vertically and absorbs the contact while contesting the driving shot attempt by O'Neale (UTA).
Bullock (DAL) and Gobert (UTA) briefly engage and disengage and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Conley (UTA) makes contact to Brunson's (DAL) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Dinwiddie (DAL) removes his arm from Mitchell's (UTA) path to bring it into a vertical position when marginal contact occurs at the end of the drive.
Kleber (DAL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.

Bogdanovic (UTA) jumps away from the baseline and back into Finney-Smith (DAL) to create the marginal contact as they come together during the driving shot attempt. Both Finney-Smith (DAL) and Kleber (DAL) make clean ball contact to block the driving shot attempt.
Dinwiddie (DAL) commits a take foul on Gobert (UTA).
Brunson (DAL) commits a take foul on Mitchell (UTA).
Brunson (DAL) commits a take foul on Mitchell (UTA).
